---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout title="Home">
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>rust-zkp</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      A minimal ZK-Rollup hand-built in Rust — cryptographic primitives, mini state machine, and an HTTP backend. No SNARK frameworks; every layer composed from scratch.
    </p>
    <div class="cta">
      <a href={`${base}/demos/`} class="btn primary">Try the playground</a>
      <a href={`${base}/notes/`} class="btn">Read the notes</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/egpivo/rust-zkp" class="btn" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View on GitHub</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="features">
    <h2>What this demonstrates</h2>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>ZKP primitives from scratch</h3>
        <p>Pedersen commitments, Sigma protocols, Fiat-Shamir transforms, Merkle membership, range proofs via bit decomposition.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Mini rollup</h3>
        <p>Account state, signed transactions with replay protection, atomic batch processing, sled-backed persistence with atomic writes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Production-style Rust backend</h3>
        <p>axum HTTP server, MPSC mempool, background batch builder, structured logging via tracing, custom error responses, CORS, full CI/CD.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Browser-side cryptography</h3>
        <p>Same Rust crypto compiled to WebAssembly. Sign a transaction in the browser, post to the deployed API, watch it get batched and applied.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="stack">
    <h2>Stack</h2>
    <p>
      <code>num-bigint</code>, <code>sha2</code> ·
      <code>axum</code>, <code>tokio</code>, <code>tower-http</code> ·
      <code>tracing</code> ·
      <code>sled</code>, <code>bincode</code> ·
      <code>clap</code>, <code>reqwest</code> ·
      <code>wasm-bindgen</code>, <code>wasm-pack</code> ·
      <code>rayon</code> ·
      Astro 4 ·
      Docker · Render · GitHub Pages · GitHub Actions
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="features">
    <h2>Approach</h2>
    <p>
      Most ZKP tutorials show toy code or jump straight to SNARK frameworks.
      This project sits in the middle: build every primitive yourself, compose them into a working system, and understand why each piece exists.
    </p>
    <p>
      The cryptography is intentionally simplified — small primes instead of elliptic curves, direct verification instead of SNARKs — to keep the focus on architecture and protocol design. The full picture of what's production-grade and what's not is in <a href={`${base}/notes/mini_rollup`}>this note</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      Built end-to-end as a learning project: ZKP exercises → rollup composition → backend → WASM playground → deployment. Notes for each layer are in the <a href={`${base}/notes/`}>Notes</a> section.
    </p>
  </section>

  <style>
    .hero {
      padding: 32px 0 48px;
    }
    .hero h1 {
      font-size: 3rem;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
      font-family: ui-monospace, "SF Mono", Menlo, monospace;
    }
    .lead {
      font-size: 1.15rem;
      color: var(--fg-muted);
      max-width: 680px;
    }
    .cta {
      margin-top: 24px;
      display: flex;
      gap: 12px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }
    .btn {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 10px 18px;
      border-radius: 6px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      background: white;
      color: var(--fg);
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: 500;
    }
    .btn:hover { border-color: var(--accent); color: var(--accent); }
    .btn.primary {
      background: var(--accent);
      color: white;
      border-color: var(--accent);
    }
    .btn.primary:hover { color: white; opacity: 0.9; }
    .features, .stack {
      margin-top: 48px;
    }
    .stack p {
      color: var(--fg-muted);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      line-height: 1.9;
    }
    .stack code {
      font-size: 0.85em;
    }
    .grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
      gap: 16px;
      margin-top: 16px;
    }
    .card {
      padding: 20px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 8px;
      background: white;
    }
    .card h3 {
      margin: 0 0 8px;
      font-size: 1.05rem;
    }
    .card p {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--fg-muted);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
